reviews.review_text: 3-16-90 Excellent show and recording. Thanks Charlie.
great night must listen sounds great brent is happy dc is always a good time well i dont know after 91

BRENT Must hear Blow Away
Testify Brother!

Third Night Cap Charlie Miller's audio- always the best. This show isn't as good as the first two nights, but it's still a spring 90 gem. Great closing night to a great run. LTGTR opener always a treat. Fantastic third quarter with the scarlet->estimated, ship of fools->women are smarter. Jam that follows is unique, worth the listen with a nice little eyes tease in the middle. Slow, sweet Stella Blue in the Jerry ballad slot. Incidentally, five songs from this show (LTGTR, Bird Song, Blow Away, Scarlet->Estimated) made the cut for the compilation, So Glad You Made It. None from 3/14 or 3/15.

3/16/1990 great show and awesome Soundboard Very good show and batch of songs they chose for that night.  As usual Charles Miller did a great job of cleaning up the show and making sound perfect.  I look for soundboards by Charles  they are my favorite.
